The object details page loads fine with objects that have '//' in the path, but the "make public" action fails with the following error...

{code}
Failed to make object foo//bar/d22529ad-e641-4d05-ae06-e904200c8253/install.log.part.0 public: The specified key does not exist.
{code}

To create an object with '//' in the path, use the following command (run as cloud admin)...

{code}
euca-import-volume ~/access.log -f raw -b testing-gui1993-bucket -z one --prefix foo//bar
{code}
